description:
Congratulations! You've built a working framework. Now let's use it to create a complete page with multiple elements.

**What you need to do:**
- Create an `h1` tag with a heading
- Create a `p` tag with some paragraph text
- Create an `a` tag (link) with `href` pointing to a URL and `target="_blank"` to open in a new tab
- There's already a button example with an `onClick` handler that shows an alert - you can use it as a reference!

**Example structure:**
```javascript
const container = document.getElementById('root') || document.body;
const heading = createElement('h1', {}, 'My Heading');
const paragraph = createElement('p', {}, 'Some text here');
const link = createElement('a', { href: 'https://example.com', target: '_blank' }, 'Click me');
const button = createElement('button', { onClick: () => alert('Almost there!') }, 'Click me');

render(heading, container);
render(paragraph, container);
render(link, container);
render(button, container);
```

**Tips:**
- Use `createElement` for each element
- Use `render` to add each element to the container
- For the link, make sure to include both `href` and `target` in the props object
- Feel free to add more elements and experiment! Try different tags, styles, or event handlers.

**Have fun!** This is your chance to play around with the framework you built. Add images, lists, forms, or anything else you can think of!
